  "texts": [
    "Typically, morphological features are extracted from each cell using classical image processing software.",
    "These so-called 'handengineered' features have been carefully developed and optimized to capture cellular morphology variations, including size, shape, intensity and texture of the various stains in the image.",
    "These features are the current standard in the field and require post-processing steps including normalization, feature selection and dimensionality Resource https://doi.org/10.1038/s41592-024-02241-6",
    "As well, it includes only a single cell type, time point and imaging condition.",
    "Thus, the nature of CPJUMP1 enables the testing of computational strategies to optimally represent the samples so that they can be compared and thus uncover valuable biological relationships."
  ],
